---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for Higher Education"
  description="The enrolment cliff is the biggest story in education — and most institutions are watching it happen to them. Earned media that makes a college, an EdTech, or an enrolment partner the name a reporter calls first."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'Higher Education' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For higher education
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The biggest story in education<br />
        is happening <em>to you.</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        The enrolment cliff, the cost-of-college reckoning, the AI-and-the-degree question — reporters are writing the future of education right now. <em>The institutions that get quoted are the ones families, boards, and partners decide to trust.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP — the desks that write education ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the education story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the education story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">THE CHRONICLE OF HIGHER EDUCATION</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">Inside Higher Ed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">EDSURGE</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">EdScoop</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-roman">Higher Ed Dive</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">The cliff is coming for<br /><em>everyone's attention.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          There are fewer eighteen-year-olds every year, and there will be for a decade. Every college knows the number. Every EdTech founder pitches against it. Every enrolment partner sells the cure for it. And every one of them says nearly the same thing to the same families, in the same week, in the same anxious voice — <em>which means none of them is heard.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">The brochure is not the byline</div>

        <p>
          A family choosing a college, a provost choosing a platform, a board choosing an OPM — they do not decide on the viewbook or the sales deck. They decide on the name they already trust. And trust is not bought with a paid campaign that runs until the budget ends. It is <strong>earned</strong> when a reporter writing about the enrolment cliff calls <em>your</em> institution for the data, when your founder is quoted on whether the degree still pays, when your name is the one already in the room before the pitch begins.
        </p>

        <p>
          The proof is sitting in your own numbers right now. Completion rates for the students everyone else writes off. Time-to-value on a credential. What your outcomes data says about the cost question that has the whole country arguing. <em>Most institutions file that under the dashboard. The ones that get remembered recognise it as the story no competitor can tell.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ WHO THIS IS FOR — three buyers, one method ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — Who this is for</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">One cliff. <em>Three rooms.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          The story is the same crisis from three angles — and the office finds the one true sentence for each. <em>Whichever room you sit in, the work begins with your data and ends with your name in print.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aud-grid">
        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the institution</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Colleges &amp; <em>Universities.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            You are fighting for mind-share in the year families decide where the tuition goes. We turn your outcomes — completion, mobility, the return on the degree — into the angle that puts your president on the page reporters are already writing.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">President · Provost · Advancement · Enrolment Marketing</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the builder</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">EdTech <em>Companies.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            Your category is loud and your funding is finite. Paid spend buys clicks that vanish; an earned story in the trade your buyers read becomes the proof point in every deck after. We mine your usage data for the claim no competitor can make.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">Founder · CMO · Head of Growth · Comms</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the partner</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Enrolment <em>Partners.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            OPMs, agencies, and bootcamps live or die on the trust of the institutions they serve. When a provost reads your name in <em>The Chronicle</em> on the right side of the value question, the next partnership conversation starts from yes.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">OPMs · Agencies · Bootcamps · Lead-gen</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">16</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">In a single semester</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Trade-tier outlets</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Chronicle · Inside Higher Ed · EdSurge</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable number</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Pulled from the outcomes data</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern holds across the cliff. We spend the first weeks finding the figure no competitor can claim — a completion gap closed, a credential that pays faster, a cohort everyone else wrote off — and the rest placing it where the deciders already read. <em>The room changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not run your enrolment funnel or write your viewbook. We build the conditions under which a family, a provost, or a board already knows your name before the decision. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the vertical.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the education desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your outcomes.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your data is one true sentence about the future of education that no competitor can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing on your homepage.</em> We sit with your institutional research until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where the deciders read.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A claim in a press release is still a press release. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right reporter at <em>The Chronicle</em> or <em>Inside Higher Ed</em> runs the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the answer when the sector asks who is getting it right.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — THE WORK ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · The work</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three engagements.<br /><em>Built for the desk.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Three ways the office goes to work on an institution, a platform, or a partner. <em>Pick the one that fits the term you are in.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement I · The fastest</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Mine the <em>outcomes story.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            We turn your existing completion, mobility, or usage data into a single reporter-ready angle on the cliff — the number an education editor cannot get anywhere else.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Audit of your outcomes data</li>
            <li>One un-ignorable thesis</li>
            <li>Reporter-ready memo</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement II · The campaign</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Own the <em>term's narrative.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A sustained placement campaign across the trades your deciders read. Your president or founder becomes the named source on the cliff, the cost question, and the AI-and-the-degree debate that decides your market.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Pitch · place · follow-up</li>
            <li>Chronicle · Inside Higher Ed · EdSurge</li>
            <li>Executive positioning</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement III · The engine</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Arm your <em>internal team.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            The earned-media skills your comms or advancement lead can run themselves — pitch craft, journalist research, the angle-finder — tuned to the education beat and built to outlast any one campaign.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Earned-media playbook</li>
            <li>Education press list</li>
            <li>Repeatable, in-house</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand institutions and platforms promising families a better future. There are perhaps a handful who can get a reporter to call them first when the sector's biggest question is being written. <em>We are built for the second problem.</em> If that is the one keeping you up, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — From the field</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What the desk <em>hears back.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            They found a completion number in our own data we had been sitting on for years. Five weeks later our provost was quoted in Inside Higher Ed on the value question. Three boards asked us how we did it.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">VP, Advancement</span>
            <span class="field-role">Regional public university</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            We had burned the quarter's budget on ads no provost remembered. One earned story in EdSurge did more for our enterprise pipeline than the entire paid push.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Founder</span>
            <span class="field-role">Early-stage EdTech platform</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            What I paid for was placements. What I got was a thesis for how we talk about partnership in a year everyone distrusts OPMs. Every conversation now starts from credibility.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Managing Director</span>
            <span class="field-role">Enrolment partner / OPM</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Names withheld where confidentiality required. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to be the name <em>they call first?</em>"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the angle hiding in your outcomes data, and tell you straight whether we can make your institution impossible for the sector to ignore."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── WHO THIS IS FOR — three-buyer segment cards ─────── */
  .aud-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .aud-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .aud-tag {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
  }
  .aud-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .aud-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .aud-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-line {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--x4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    color: var(--claret);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .field-role {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--x5);
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .aud-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .eng-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
